    <item>
      <title>Escaping Windows</title>
      <link>https://gasparvardanyan.github.io/blog/escaping-windows/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 16 Oct 2022 03:41:37 +0400</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://gasparvardanyan.github.io/blog/escaping-windows/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m a C++ software engineer. I have to build projects running on MS Windows.
The beginning was &lt;a href=&#34;https://xn--69aa8bzb.xn--y9a3aq/web/@gaspar/109030661073651505&#34;&gt;very stressfull&lt;/a&gt;&amp;hellip;
I&amp;rsquo;ve had to navigate my windows in Windows&amp;rsquo; stupid desktop, started using mouse :d,
I&amp;rsquo;ve started to use &lt;strong&gt;Visual Studio&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Qt Creator&lt;/strong&gt; with incomplete and annoying
&amp;lsquo;vim mode&amp;rsquo; plugins. I&amp;rsquo;ve lost my productivity!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve even changed the OS on my personal laptop to Windows 10 to get comfortable
with it, to do my job faster, but&amp;hellip; to me remember that was the first time I&amp;rsquo;ve
heard the sound of my laptop&amp;rsquo;s cooler (after swithing to linux).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve installed &lt;strong&gt;NeoVIM&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;qutebrowser&lt;/strong&gt;, etc on my windows desktop, but&amp;hellip;
I&amp;rsquo;ve always had high &lt;strong&gt;CPU&lt;/strong&gt; usage, so called &lt;strong&gt;Antimalware Service Executable&lt;/strong&gt;
in &lt;strong&gt;Task Manager&lt;/strong&gt; (and other sh&lt;em&gt;ts), &lt;strong&gt;Edge&lt;/strong&gt; (շան երեսին ինչքան կանջատես, էլի
ինքն իրան կմիանա վախտմ հետո) 4GB RAM usage (closed all windows), almost
everything was slow (even icons were slowly loading in Task Manager :d), and a
lot of stuff on my desktop (files, folders&amp;hellip; unorganized workflow), plusss&amp;hellip;
MS tracking sh&lt;/em&gt;ts, ads, License problem (ofc KMS Auto solved it) and STRESS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;and-this-is-how-ive-escaped-windows-masochism&#34;&gt;And This is How I&amp;rsquo;ve Escaped Windows Masochism!&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;ve reinstalled &lt;strong&gt;ArchLinux&lt;/strong&gt; on my laptop, mounted my computer&amp;rsquo;s (Windows 10)
filesystem (user&amp;rsquo;s &amp;lsquo;home&amp;rsquo; folder) over lan:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo mount -t cifs -o &lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;user&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#719e07&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;USER,pass&lt;span style=&#34;color:#719e07&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;PASSWORD,noperm //DESKTOP/USER &lt;span style=&#34;color:#268bd2&#34;&gt;$HOME&lt;/span&gt;/windows
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;and connected to my computer&amp;rsquo;s desktop via &lt;strong&gt;FreeRDP&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#93a1a1;background-color:#002b36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;xfreerdp /u:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;DESKTOP\USER&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; /p:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;PASSWORD&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; /v:&lt;span style=&#34;color:#2aa198&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;COMPUTERS_LOCAL_IP&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; /dynamic-resolution -grab-keyboard
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;../2022-10-16-042344_1366x768_scrot.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now I edit my code in VIM, switch to Windows Desktop (Super+Tab) and press F5
(there&amp;rsquo;s only the Visual Studio open to compile and run my code). Now my workflow
is the same as it was.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;hellip; Why RDP and not something like AnyDesk? Because AnyDesk is very slow,
uncomfortable and closed source proprietary garbage (maybe RDP (server) too, but
the client I use on my laptop is FOSS)!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Easy Channel List Player</title>
